reviews.review_text:
tasty sounds!! The show is a good one. The Good Ole Boys are defined as "ON" in this show.
I remember wanting to be the Great American VITAMIN salesman the fall before after my first show at Alpine '89 so I could wander all over Europe during this fall tour abroad.The songs and the instruments as well as the vocals are "Dead On" for this performance. Recording is excellent.

Liked this best of Europe '90 I guess outside of the absurd ICC shows this was my favorite.  This is a great city and had a Wharf Rat feel to it.  The gym was just made for the Boys.

I took my jets to Europe, and it was a good move.  We grooved with Chet and his mom at most of these shows.  I hope they are doing well.
